cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.OH

Reasoning: 

- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a method for aligning software-related activities with high-level business goals. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the impact of the method on organizational goals and strategies. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper discusses the alignment of goals at all levels of an organization. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possibility as the paper discusses the identification of impediments to achieving goals. 
- cs.OH (Other Computer Science) is a possibility as the paper does not fit neatly into any of the other categories and covers a broad range of topics related to organizational alignment.
